# Simplify to Single Daily Prompt - Implementation Instructions

## 1. Update Quote Model
   Remove the separate morning/evening prompts and replace with single daily prompt:

   ```swift
   struct Quote {
       let id: UUID
       let text: String
       let author: String
       let sourceType: String
       let executiveContext: String
       let topics: [String]
       let dailyPrompt: String  // CHANGED: Renamed from morningPrompt
       // REMOVED: eveningReflection
   }
   ```

## 2. Update All Existing Quotes
   For each quote in QuoteData.swift:
   - Remove `eveningReflection` property
   - Rename `morningPrompt` to `dailyPrompt`
   - Rewrite prompts to be deeper, more reflective

   Example transformation:
   ```swift
   // OLD:
   morningPrompt: "What external pressures will you face today that you cannot control?",
   eveningReflection: "Which situations today did you handle by focusing on your response?"

   // NEW:
   dailyPrompt: "Think of a current challenge consuming your mental energy. What aspects are truly within your control, and what would happen if you fully released attachment to the rest?"
   ```

## 3. Update QuoteView UI
   In the quote detail view:
   - Add new section titled "Today's Reflection" or "Daily Prompt"
   - Display the prompt prominently
   - Add a "Set Reminder" button next to the prompt

   ```swift
   VStack(alignment: .leading, spacing: 12) {
       Text("Today's Reflection")
           .font(.headline)
           .foregroundColor(.secondary)

       Text(quote.dailyPrompt)
           .font(.body)
           .padding()
           .background(Color.gray.opacity(0.1))
           .cornerRadius(8)

       Button(action: { schedulePromptReminder() }) {
           Label("Set Reminder", systemImage: "bell")
               .font(.caption)
       }
   }
   ```

## 4. Update Notification System
   In NotificationManager.swift:

   ### Add new notification type:
   ```swift
   enum NotificationType {
       case dailyQuote      // Existing morning quote
       case dailyPrompt     // New prompt reminder
   }
   ```

   ### Add prompt reminder scheduling:
   ```swift
   func schedulePromptReminder(for date: Date, prompt: String) {
       let content = UNMutableNotificationContent()
       content.title = "Time for Reflection"
       content.body = prompt
       content.sound = .default

       let components = Calendar.current.dateComponents([.hour, .minute], from: date)
       let trigger = UNCalendarNotificationTrigger(dateMatching: components, repeats: false)

       let request = UNNotificationRequest(
           identifier: "prompt-\(date.timeIntervalSince1970)",
           content: content,
           trigger: trigger
       )

       UNUserNotificationCenter.current().add(request)
   }
   ```

## 5. Update Settings View
   Add new settings for prompt notifications:

   ```swift
   Section("Daily Prompt Notifications") {
       Toggle("Enable Prompt Reminders", isOn: $enablePromptNotifications)
           .onChange(of: enablePromptNotifications) { newValue in
               if !newValue {
                   notificationManager.cancelAllPromptReminders()
               }
           }

       if enablePromptNotifications {
           Text("Set reminder when viewing daily quote")
               .font(.caption)
               .foregroundColor(.secondary)
       }
   }
   ```

## 6. Add Prompt Reminder UI
   In QuoteDetailView, when user taps "Set Reminder":

   ```swift
   .sheet(isPresented: $showingReminderPicker) {
       VStack {
           Text("Set Reflection Reminder")
               .font(.headline)
               .padding()

           DatePicker("Remind me at:", 
                     selection: $reminderTime, 
                     displayedComponents: .hourAndMinute)
               .datePickerStyle(WheelDatePickerStyle())
               .labelsHidden()

           HStack {
               Button("Cancel") { 
                   showingReminderPicker = false 
               }

               Spacer()

               Button("Set Reminder") {
                   notificationManager.schedulePromptReminder(
                       for: reminderTime,
                       prompt: quote.dailyPrompt
                   )
                   showingReminderPicker = false
                   // Show confirmation
               }
           }
           .padding()
       }
   }
   ```

## 7. Update UserDefaults
   Track prompt notification preferences:

   ```swift
   extension UserDefaults {
       var enablePromptNotifications: Bool {
           get { bool(forKey: "enablePromptNotifications") }
           set { set(newValue, forKey: "enablePromptNotifications") }
       }

       // Store which prompts have reminders set
       var scheduledPromptDates: [String] {
           get { stringArray(forKey: "scheduledPromptDates") ?? [] }
           set { set(newValue, forKey: "scheduledPromptDates") }
       }
   }
   ```

## 8. Rewrite All Daily Prompts
   Transform existing prompts to be deeper and more executive-focused:

   ### Examples of new prompt style:
   ```swift
   // Quote: "You have power over your mind—not outside events."
   dailyPrompt: "Consider the biggest stressor in your leadership right now. If you had zero ability to change the external situation but unlimited power over your response, what would shift in your approach? What are you trying to control that you actually can't?"

   // Quote: "Discipline equals freedom."
   dailyPrompt: "Where in your organization is lack of process creating constant firefighting? Choose one area where implementing disciplined systems would free your team's creative energy. What's preventing you from starting this week?"

   // Quote: "Only the paranoid survive."
   dailyPrompt: "What industry assumption does everyone accept as permanent that could be disrupted within 18 months? If you knew your biggest competitor was already building for this future, what would you start tomorrow?"
   ```

## 9. Default Settings
   In app initialization:
   - Daily quote notification: ON (existing)
   - Daily prompt notification: OFF (new)
   - Users must explicitly enable prompt reminders

## 10. Notification Management
   - Only one prompt reminder active at a time
   - Setting new reminder cancels previous
   - Reminder automatically clears after firing
   - Option to cancel reminder from quote view

